{% extends 'LaDanseSiteBundle:layout:page-centered.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Guild Chat & Voice - La Danse Macabre{% endblock %}

{% block memberPageCenteredBody %}

    {{ renderHeader('Discord Bot Gnomie Help') }}

    <div class="BotHelpContainer">

        <p>
            If you mark your sign up as "Will Come" it means that you intend to be there at invite time and you
            currently have no reason to believe you won't be able to come.
        </p>

        <p class="BotCommandHeader">!help</p>

        <p>
            Use this command to get a URL to this help page.
        </p>

        <p class="BotCommandHeader">!raids</p>

        <p>
            Show the list of raids for the next 4 weeks. For each raid the bot lists the name, the day of the week
            and the invite time. It also gives details on the number of people signed up in the form of "(x/y - z)".
            "x" is the number of people who signed as "Will Come", y is the number of people who signed "Might Come"
            and "z" is the number of people who informed us of their absence.
        </p>

        <p>
            Each raid is followed by a link going straight to the sign up page for this event.
        </p>

        <div class="BotExample">
            <p class="UserTag">Leto/Tanidia</p>
            <p>!raids</p>
            <br/>
            <p class="UserTag">Gnomie</p>
            <p>Upcoming raids from https://www.ladanse.org/</p>
            <br/>
            <p>Antorus, the Burning Throne (Normal) on Fri 8/12 19:15 - (12/2 - 3)</p>
            <p>https://www.ladanse.org/app/events#/events/event/123</p>
        </div>

        <p class="BotCommandHeader">!hello</p>

        <p>
            For some commands (e.g. see !sign) the bot needs to be able to act in your name on the website. You
            can use this command to initiate a process that will allow you to authorize the bot. If you don't do
            this, it will be initiated when you issue a command for which the bot needs to be able to act
            in your name on the website.
        </p>

        <p>
            Note that part of this process continues in a private chat between you and the bot. So make sure to
            check your private messages in your Discord client!
        </p>

        <p class="BotCommandHeader">!sign</p>

        <p>
            With this command you can sign up for a raid. Form a sentence like the one below:
        </p>

        <div class="BotExample">
            <p class="UserTag">Leto/Tanidia</p>
            <p>!sign will come for 17/02 as healer and dps</p>
        </div>

        <p>
            The sentence always starts with the command "!sign", next comes either "will come", "might come"
            or "absent", followed by a date and, optionally, a list of roles you want to sign up for.
        </p>

        <p>
            If you haven't signed up for the raid on the given, the bot will sign you up. If you had already signed
            up the bot will update your sign up to reflect what you wrote in the command.
        </p>

        <p>
            You currently can't remove your sign up (but you can change it to "Absent".
        </p>

    </div>

{% endblock %}

